replies.body:
Not to long ago I wrote a piece on **Ezreal **(http://community.na.leagueoflegends.com/en/c/miscellaneous/FGp9u6s1-character-analysis-ezreal-and-indiana-jones), talking about how the character could be more thematically appropriate.

As it stands now Ezreal does not really fill the fantasy of the explorer and his only defining trait is arrogance, making him a kind of disagreeable character to play. Considering how well liked the character is and how often played, I think he's in a good place for a **low risk/high reward** VU; something along the lines of Garen. Perhaps a few model tweeks and texture clean up. The guy could also use a revamped dialogue, because it's really lacking as is.

I see Ezreal as a young, talented, but egotistical young Indiana Jones; think River Pheonix's portrayal in *Indiana Jones: The Last Crusade*. While I think his kit is fine for the most part, everything else about him screams...outdated. I'm sure he's very low on the list, but he's high on mine. {{champion:81}}

What about the rock? He got a nice splash but he's quite ugly if I do say so myself :x {{champion:54}} 

Also when are we getting the new WW? :D{{champion:19}}

{{champion:154}} (Still waiting on Pool Party Zac){{champion:154}}
